<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>   
Chapter 4</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>And in that day seven women shall take hold of one man, saying, We will  
eat our own bread, and wear our own apparel: only let us be called by thy name, 
to take away our reproach.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4>
</TD><TD><P>In that day shall the branch of YHVH be beautiful and glorious, and 
the fruit of the earth shall be excellent and comely for them that are escaped  
of Israel.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>And 
it shall come to pass, that he that is left in Zion, and he that remaineth in   
Jerusalem, shall be called holy, even every one that is written among the       
living in Jerusalem:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>When the ADONAY shall have washed away the filth of the daughters of     
Zion, and shall have purged the blood of Jerusalem from the midst thereof by    
the spirit of judgment, and by the spirit of burning.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD      
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH will create upon every     
dwelling place of mount Zion, and upon her assemblies, a cloud and smoke by     
day, and the shining of a flaming fire by night: for upon all the glory shall   
be a defence.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P> 
And there shall be a tabernacle for a shadow in the day time from the heat, and 
for a place of refuge, and for a covert from storm and from rain.</P></TD></TR> 
